{"by": "kgeist", "id": 43182544, "parent": 43159250, "text": "Russian has a similar distinction: if there are two &quot;he&#x27;s&quot;, you can use &quot;on&quot; (proximate) and &quot;tot&quot; (distant) to distinguish between them. Like,<p><pre><code>  &quot;he (on) said it was okay, but he (tot) disagreed&quot;.\n</code></pre>\nIn this example, the first &quot;he&quot; is the person with the main focus in the conversation, and &quot;tot&quot; is someone else who was also mentioned but is not the main focus.", "time": 1740566423, "type": "comment"}